            <m:mrow>
              <m:mn>1</m:mn>
              <m:mo>−</m:mo>
              <m:mfrac>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mi>v</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mi>c</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
              </m:mfrac>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mfenced>
        </m:msqrt>
      </m:mrow>
    </m:mfrac>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>

</para>
<para id="element-61">
where mo is rest mass and c is the speed of light in vacuum. The particle becomes heavier at higher speed. Putting this in the expression of frequency, we have :

</para>
<para id="element-62">
<m:math display="block">
